{{see|Guinea}}

== English ==
===Etymology 1===
From {{E.}} "[[Guinea]] [[negro]]", based upon the popular beliefs that Italians were part African because of (a) their darker skin, or (b) former Moorish domination of parts of southern Italy.
====Noun====
'''guinea'''
#(''United States English slang, pejorative'') a person of [[Italian]] descent
